<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="302" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[159,1156,905,1243]" box="[160,262,905,931]" pageId="37" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,905,931]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="302">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[159,1156,905,1243]" pageId="37" pageNumber="302">
<taxonomicName box="[160,344,941,966]" class="Gastropoda" family="Siphonariidae" genus="Williamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonariida" pageId="37" pageNumber="302" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gussoni">
<emphasis box="[160,344,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="302">Williamia gussoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be confused with the sympatric 
<taxonomicName authority="(O. F. Muller, 1776)" baseAuthorityName="O. F. Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[776,1152,941,966]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lottiidae" genus="Tectura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonariida" pageId="37" pageNumber="302" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="virginea">
<emphasis box="[776,944,941,966]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="302">Tectura virginea</emphasis>
(O.F. Müller, 1776)
</taxonomicName>
, from which it can be distinguished by the absence of long oral tentacles typical of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[1017,1095,975,1000]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lottiidae" genus="Tectura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonariida" pageId="37" pageNumber="302" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1017,1095,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="302">Tectura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.Also, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[185,263,1010,1035]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lottiidae" genus="Tectura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonariida" pageId="37" pageNumber="302" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[185,263,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="302">Tectura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the apical part of the shell is in the anterior segment of the body, near the head. The pattern of the shell ribs is also different, with a greater number of vertical and more irregularly distributed white lines. Remarkably, the photograph herein is, to our knowledge, the first one taken of live 
<taxonomicName box="[299,412,1114,1139]" class="Gastropoda" family="Siphonariidae" genus="Williamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonariida" pageId="37" pageNumber="302" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gussoni">
<emphasis box="[299,412,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="302">W. gussoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens in their habitat. This species has been widely cited based only on shells found on sediments,with scarce data on living specimens,related to red algae of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Decaisne, 1841" authorityName="Decaisne" authorityYear="1841" box="[290,615,1183,1208]" family="Peyssonneliaceae" genus="Peyssonnelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cryptonemiales" pageId="37" pageNumber="302" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[290,426,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="302">Peyssonnelia</emphasis>
Decaisne, 1841
</taxonomicName>
. In our study, we observed a specimen from 
<date box="[160,339,1218,1243]" pageId="37" pageNumber="302" value="2020-10-31">31 October 2020</date>
until 
<date box="[401,590,1218,1243]" pageId="37" pageNumber="302" value="2021-02-27">27 February 2021</date>
, always on the same algal frond of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boudouresque and Denizot" authorityYear="1973" box="[968,1120,1218,1243]" family="Peyssonneliaceae" genus="Peyssonnelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cryptonemiales" pageId="37" pageNumber="302" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="species" species="rosa-marina">
<emphasis box="[968,1120,1218,1243]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="302">P. rosa-marina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
